      <hedline>
        <hl1>Housing Is a Priority</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by HUD Deputy Asst Sec Lisa MacSpadden says that Sec Andrew Cuomo did indeed mention need for 'affordable housing' in his speech at Democratic national convention (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An Aug. 27 letter says it is ''paradoxical'' that Housing Secretary Andrew M. Cuomo would fail to mention the need for affordable housing in his speech to the Democratic National Convention.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An Aug. 27 letter says it is ''paradoxical'' that Housing Secretary Andrew M. Cuomo would fail to mention the need for affordable housing in his speech to the Democratic National Convention.</p>
        <p>In fact, Mr. Cuomo's remarks were abbreviated in your Aug. 22 news article, to which the letter writer referred. Mr. Cuomo said: ''Imagine how strong we're going to be when we help our working families with affordable college educations and affordable health care and affordable housing.''</p>
        <p>In the seven years that Mr. Cuomo has been at HUD, no one has spoken more forcefully and eloquently about the American people's need for affordable housing. I am glad to see  Mr. Cuomo's calls for more affordable housing being echoed in your pages.</p>
        <p>LISA MAC SPADDEN  Deputy Asst. Secy. for  Public Affairs, Dept. of  Housing and Urban Development  Washington, Aug. 30, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
